(1, 'Cricket', 'cricket', 'Cricket in south asia', '\\images\\blogimages\\MFCLB21625106592.jpg', '<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><b>Cricket</b>&nbsp;is a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bat-and-ball_games\" title=\"Bat-and-ball games\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">bat-and-ball game</a>&nbsp;played between two teams of eleven players on a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket_field\" title=\"Cricket field\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">field</a>&nbsp;at the centre of which is a 22-yard (20-metre)&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket_pitch\" title=\"Cricket pitch\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">pitch</a>&nbsp;with a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wicket\" title=\"Wicket\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">wicket</a>&nbsp;at each end, each comprising two&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bail_(cricket)\" title=\"Bail (cricket)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">bails</a>&nbsp;balanced on three&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stump_(cricket)\" title=\"Stump (cricket)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">stumps</a>. The&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Batting_(cricket)\" title=\"Batting (cricket)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">batting</a>&nbsp;side scores&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Run_(cricket)\" title=\"Run (cricket)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">runs</a>&nbsp;by striking the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket_ball\" title=\"Cricket ball\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">ball</a>&nbsp;bowled at the wicket with the bat (and running between the wickets), while the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bowling_(cricket)\" title=\"Bowling (cricket)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">bowling</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fielding_(cricket)\" title=\"Fielding (cricket)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">fielding</a>&nbsp;side tries to prevent this (by preventing the ball from leaving the field, and getting the ball to either wicket) and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dismissal_(cricket)\" title=\"Dismissal (cricket)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">dismiss</a>&nbsp;each batter (so they are \"out\"). Means of dismissal include being&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bowled\" title=\"Bowled\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">bowled</a>, when the ball hits the stumps and dislodges the bails, and by the fielding side either&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caught\" title=\"Caught\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">catching</a>&nbsp;the ball after it is hit by the bat and before it hits the ground, or hitting a wicket with the ball before a batter can cross the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crease_(cricket)\" title=\"Crease (cricket)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">crease</a>&nbsp;in front of the wicket. When ten batters have been dismissed, the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Innings\" title=\"Innings\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">innings</a>&nbsp;ends and the teams swap roles. The game is adjudicated by two&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Umpire_(cricket)\" title=\"Umpire (cricket)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">umpires</a>, aided by a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Third_umpire\" title=\"Third umpire\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">third umpire</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Match_referee\" title=\"Match referee\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">match referee</a>&nbsp;in international matches.</p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Forms_of_cricket\" title=\"Forms of cricket\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Forms of cricket</a>&nbsp;range from&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Twenty20\" title=\"Twenty20\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Twenty20</a>, with each team batting for a single innings of 20&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Over_(cricket)\" title=\"Over (cricket)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">overs</a>, to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Test_cricket\" title=\"Test cricket\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Test matches</a>&nbsp;played over five days. Traditionally cricketers play in all-white&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket_clothing_and_equipment\" title=\"Cricket clothing and equipment\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">kit</a>, but in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Limited_overs_cricket\" title=\"Limited overs cricket\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">limited overs cricket</a>&nbsp;they wear club or team colours. In addition to the basic kit, some players wear&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket_clothing_and_equipment\" title=\"Cricket clothing and equipment\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">protective gear</a>&nbsp;to prevent injury caused by the ball, which is a hard, solid spheroid made of compressed&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leather\" title=\"Leather\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">leather</a>&nbsp;with a slightly raised sewn seam enclosing a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cork_(material)\" title=\"Cork (material)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">cork</a>&nbsp;core layered with tightly wound string.</p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">The earliest reference to cricket is in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_East_England\" title=\"South East England\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">South East England</a>&nbsp;in the mid-16th century. It spread globally with the expansion of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British_Empire\" title=\"British Empire\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">British Empire</a>, with the first international matches in the second half of the 19th century. The game\'s governing body is the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Cricket_Council\" title=\"International Cricket Council\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">International Cricket Council</a>&nbsp;(ICC), which has over 100 members, twelve of which are&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_International_Cricket_Council_members\" title=\"List of International Cricket Council members\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">full members</a>&nbsp;who play Test matches. The game\'s rules, the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Laws_of_Cricket\" title=\"Laws of Cricket\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Laws of Cricket</a>, are maintained by&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marylebone_Cricket_Club\" title=\"Marylebone Cricket Club\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Marylebone Cricket Club</a>&nbsp;(MCC) in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/London\" title=\"London\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">London</a>. The sport is followed primarily in the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indian_subcontinent\" title=\"Indian subcontinent\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Indian subcontinent</a>, Australasia, the United Kingdom,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Southern_Africa\" title=\"Southern Africa\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">southern Africa</a>&nbsp;and the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/West_Indies\" title=\"West Indies\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">West Indies</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-1\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[1]</a></sup>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Women%27s_cricket\" title=\"Women\'s cricket\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Women\'s cricket</a>, which is organised and played separately, has also achieved international standard. The most successful side playing&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_cricket\" title=\"International cricket\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">international cricket</a>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australia_national_cricket_team\" title=\"Australia national cricket team\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Australia</a>, which has won seven&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One_Day_International\" title=\"One Day International\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">One Day International</a>&nbsp;trophies, including five&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket_World_Cup\" title=\"Cricket World Cup\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">World Cups</a>, more than any other country and has been the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ICC_Test_Championship\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"ICC Test Championship\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">top-rated Test side</a>&nbsp;more than any other country.</p><div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\" role=\"navigation\" aria-labelledby=\"mw-toc-heading\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); padding: 7px; font-size: 13.3px; display: table; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif;\"