display: table-cell; text-decoration: inherit;\">In the arts and popular culture</span></a></li><li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-36\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.1em;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#Influence_on_other_sports\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span class=\"tocnumber\" style=\"display: table-cell; text-decoration: inherit; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0.5em;\">7.3</span><span class=\"toctext\" style=\"display: table-cell; text-decoration: inherit;\">Influence on other sports</span></a></li></ul></li><li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-37\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.1em;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#See_also\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span class=\"tocnumber\" style=\"display: table-cell; text-decoration: inherit; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0.5em;\">8</span><span class=\"toctext\" style=\"display: table-cell; text-decoration: inherit;\">See also</span></a></li><li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-38\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.1em;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#Footnotes\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span class=\"tocnumber\" style=\"display: table-cell; text-decoration: inherit; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0.5em;\">9</span><span class=\"toctext\" style=\"display: table-cell; text-decoration: inherit;\">Footnotes</span></a></li><li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-39\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.1em;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#Citations\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span class=\"tocnumber\" style=\"display: table-cell; text-decoration: inherit; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0.5em;\">10</span><span class=\"toctext\" style=\"display: table-cell; text-decoration: inherit;\">Citations</span></a></li><li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-40\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.1em;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#General_sources\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span class=\"tocnumber\" style=\"display: table-cell; text-decoration: inherit; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0.5em;\">11</span><span class=\"toctext\" style=\"display: table-cell; text-decoration: inherit;\">General sources</span></a></li><li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-41\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.1em;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#Further_reading\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span class=\"tocnumber\" style=\"display: table-cell; text-decoration: inherit; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0.5em;\">12</span><span class=\"toctext\" style=\"display: table-cell; text-decoration: inherit;\">Further reading</span></a></li><li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-42\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.1em;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#External_links\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span class=\"tocnumber\" style=\"display: table-cell; text-decoration: inherit; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0.5em;\">13</span><span class=\"toctext\" style=\"display: table-cell; text-decoration: inherit;\">External links</span></a></li></ul></div><h2 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 1em 0px 0.25em; padding: 0px; overflow: hidden; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177); font-size: 1.5em; font-family: &quot;Linux Libertine&quot;, Georgia, Times, serif; line-height: 1.3;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span></h2><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic; padding-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Main article:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/History_of_cricket\" title=\"History of cricket\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">History of cricket</a></div><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 0.3em 0px 0px; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-weight: bold; font-family: sans-serif;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Origins\">Origins</span></h3><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic; padding-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Main article:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/History_of_cricket_to_1725\" title=\"History of cricket to 1725\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">History of cricket to 1725</a></div><div class=\"thumb tright\" style=\"clear: right; float: right; margin: 0.5em 0px 1.3em 1.4em; width: auto; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"min-width: 100px; border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); padding: 3px; background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); font-size: 13.16px; text-align: center; overflow: hidden; width: 222px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Cantigas_de_Santa_Mar%C3%ADa_-_Xogo_da_pelota.jpg\" class=\"image\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/38/Cantigas_de_Santa_Mar%C3%ADa_-_Xogo_da_pelota.jpg/220px-Cantigas_de_Santa_Mar%C3%ADa_-_Xogo_da_pelota.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"220\" height=\"210\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/38/Cantigas_de_Santa_Mar%C3%ADa_-_Xogo_da_pelota.jpg 1.5x\" data-file-width=\"300\" data-file-height=\"286\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"></a><div class=\"thumbcaption\" style=\"border: 0px; line-height: 1.4em; padding: 3px; font-size: 12.3704px; text-align: left;\"><div class=\"magnify\" style=\"float: right; margin-left: 3px; margin-right: 0px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Cantigas_de_Santa_Mar%C3%ADa_-_Xogo_da_pelota.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: linear-gradient(transparent, transparent), url(&quot;/w/resources/src/mediawiki.skinning/images/magnify-clip-ltr.svg?8330e&quot;); background-position-x: initial, initial; background-position-y: initial, initial; background-size: initial, initial; background-repeat: repeat, repeat; background-attachment: initial, initial; background-origin: initial, initial; background-clip: initial, initial; display: block; text-indent: 15px; white-space: nowrap; overflow: hidden; width: 15px; height: 11px; user-select: none;\"></a></div>A medieval \"club ball\" game involving an underhand bowl towards a batsman. Ball catchers are shown positioning themselves to catch a ball. Detail from the&nbsp;<i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cantigas_de_Santa_Maria\" title=\"Cantigas de Santa Maria\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Canticles of Holy Mary</a></i>, 13th century.</div></div></div><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Cricket is one of many games in the \"club ball\" sphere that basically involve hitting a ball with a hand-held implement; others include&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baseball\" title=\"Baseball\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">baseball</a>&nbsp;(which shares many&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Comparison_of_baseball_and_cricket\" title=\"Comparison of baseball and cricket\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">similarities</a>&nbsp;with cricket, both belonging in the more specific&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bat-and-ball_games\" title=\"Bat-and-ball games\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">bat-and-ball games</a>&nbsp;category<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-2\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup>),&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Golf\" title=\"Golf\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">golf</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hockey\" title=\"Hockey\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">hockey</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tennis\" title=\"Tennis\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">tennis</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Squash_(sport)\" title=\"Squash (sport)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">squash</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Badminton\" title=\"Badminton\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">badminton</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Table_tennis\" title=\"Table tennis\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">table tennis</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-JM17_3-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-JM17-3\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[3]</a></sup>&nbsp;In cricket\'s case, a key difference is the existence of a solid target structure, the wicket (originally, it is thought, a \"wicket gate\" through which sheep were herded), that the batsman must defend.<sup id=\"cite_ref-BWC1_4-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-BWC1-4\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[4]</a></sup>&nbsp;The cricket historian&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harry_Altham\" title=\"Harry Altham\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Harry Altham</a>&nbsp;identified three \"groups\" of \"club ball\" games: the \"hockey group\", in which the ball is driven to and fro between two targets (the goals); the \"golf group\", in which the ball is driven towards an undefended target (the hole); and the \"cricket group\", in which \"the ball is aimed at a mark (the wicket) and driven away from it\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-HSA19_5-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-HSA19-5\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[5]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">It is generally believed that cricket originated as a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Children%27s_game\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Children\'s game\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">children\'s game</a>&nbsp;in the south-eastern counties of England, sometime during the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/England_in_the_Middle_Ages\" title=\"England in the Middle Ages\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">medieval period</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-BWC1_4-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-BWC1-4\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[4]</a></sup>&nbsp;Although there are claims for prior dates, the earliest definite reference to cricket being played comes from evidence given at a court case in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guildford\" title=\"Guildford\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Guildford</a>&nbsp;on Monday, 17 January 1597 (<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Julian_calendar\" title=\"Julian calendar\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Julian calendar</a>; equating to 30 January 1598 in the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gregorian_calendar\" title=\"Gregorian calendar\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Gregorian calendar</a>). The case concerned ownership of a certain plot of land and the court heard the testimony of a 59-year-old&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coroner\" title=\"Coroner\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">coroner</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Derrick_(coroner)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"John Derrick (coroner)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">John Derrick</a>, who gave witness that:<sup id=\"cite_ref-HSA21_6-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-HSA21-6\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[6]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-DU3_7-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-DU3-7\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[7]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-JM19_8-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-JM19-8\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[8]</a></sup></p><blockquote style=\"overflow: hidden; margin: 1em 0px; padding: 8px 32px; border-left: none; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Being a scholler in the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Royal_Grammar_School,_Guildford\" title=\"Royal Grammar School, Guildford\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">ffree schoole of Guldeford</a>&nbsp;hee and diverse of his fellows did runne and play there at creckett and other plaies.</p></blockquote><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Given Derrick\'s age, it was about half a century earlier when he was at school and so it is certain that cricket was being played c. 1550 by boys in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surrey\" title=\"Surrey\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Surrey</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-JM19_8-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-JM19-8\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[8]</a></sup>&nbsp;The view that it was originally a children\'s game is reinforced by&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Randle_Cotgrave\" title=\"Randle Cotgrave\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Randle Cotgrave</a>\'s 1611 English-French dictionary in which he defined the noun \"<i>crosse</i><span style=\"padding-left: 0.15em;\">\"</span>&nbsp;as \"the crooked staff wherewith boys play at cricket\" and the verb form \"<i>crosser</i><span style=\"padding-left: 0.15em;\">\"</span>&nbsp;as \"to play at cricket\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-HSA22_9-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-HSA22-9\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[9]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-JM31_10-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-JM31-10\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[10]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><sup id=\"cite_ref-JM31_10-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><br></sup></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><img src=\"/media/common_media/MF8I7W1624701907.jpg\" data-filename=\"common_media/MF8I7W1624701907.jpg\"><sup id=\"cite_ref-JM31_10-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><br></sup></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">One possible source for the sport\'s name is the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_English_language\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Old English language\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Old English</a>&nbsp;word \"<i>cryce</i><span style=\"padding-left: 0.15em;\">\"</span>&nbsp;(or \"<i>cricc</i><span style=\"padding-left: 0.15em;\">\"</span>) meaning a crutch or staff. In&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samuel_Johnson\" title=\"Samuel Johnson\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Samuel Johnson</a>\'s&nbsp;<i>Dictionary</i>, he derived cricket from \"<i>cryce</i>, Saxon, a stick\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-HSA21_6-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-HSA21-6\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[6]</a></sup>&nbsp;In&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_French\" title=\"Old French\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Old French</a>, the word \"<i>criquet</i><span style=\"padding-left: 0.15em;\">\"</span>&nbsp;seems to have meant a kind of club or stick.<sup id=\"cite_ref-DB3_11-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-DB3-11\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[11]</a></sup>&nbsp;Given the strong medieval trade connections between south-east England and the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/County_of_Flanders\" title=\"County of Flanders\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">County of Flanders</a>&nbsp;when the latter belonged to the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Duchy_of_Burgundy\" title=\"Duchy of Burgundy\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Duchy of Burgundy</a>, the name may have been derived from the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Middle_Dutch\" title=\"Middle Dutch\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Middle Dutch</a>&nbsp;(in use in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/County_of_Flanders\" title=\"County of Flanders\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Flanders</a>&nbsp;at the time) \"<i>krick</i><span style=\"padding-left: 0.15em;\">\"</span>(<i>-e</i>), meaning a stick (crook).<sup id=\"cite_ref-DB3_11-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-DB3-11\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[11]</a></sup>&nbsp;Another possible source is the Middle Dutch word \"<i>krickstoel</i><span style=\"padding-left: 0.15em;\">\"</span>, meaning a long low stool used for kneeling in church and which resembled the long low&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wicket\" title=\"Wicket\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">wicket</a>&nbsp;with two&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stump_(cricket)\" title=\"Stump (cricket)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">stumps</a>&nbsp;used in early cricket.<sup id=\"cite_ref-12\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-12\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[12]</a></sup>&nbsp;According to Heiner Gillmeister, a European language expert of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bonn_University\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bonn University\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Bonn University</a>, \"cricket\" derives from the Middle Dutch phrase for&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hockey\" title=\"Hockey\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">hockey</a>,&nbsp;<i>met de (krik ket)sen</i>&nbsp;(i.e., \"with the stick chase\").<sup id=\"cite_ref-17CGC_13-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-17CGC-13\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[13]</a></sup>&nbsp;Gillmeister has suggested that not only the name but also the sport itself may be of Flemish origin.<sup id=\"cite_ref-17CGC_13-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-17CGC-13\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[13]</a></sup></p><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 0.3em 0px 0px; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-weight: bold; font-family: sans-serif;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Growth_of_amateur_and_professional_cricket_in_England\">Growth of amateur and professional cricket in England</span></h3><div class=\"thumb tright\" style=\"clear: right; float: right; margin: 0.5em 0px 1.3em 1.4em; width: auto; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"min-width: 100px; border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); padding: 3px; background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); font-size: 13.16px; text-align: center; overflow: hidden; width: 222px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Historical_cricket_bat_art.jpg\" class=\"image\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dc/Historical_cricket_bat_art.jpg/220px-Historical_cricket_bat_art.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"220\" height=\"199\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dc/Historical_cricket_bat_art.jpg/330px-Historical_cricket_bat_art.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dc/Historical_cricket_bat_art.jpg/440px-Historical_cricket_bat_art.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"956\" data-file-height=\"866\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"></a><div class=\"thumbcaption\" style=\"border: 0px; line-height: 1.4em; padding: 3px; font-size: 12.3704px; text-align: left;\"><div class=\"magnify\" style=\"float: right; margin-left: 3px; margin-right: 0px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Historical_cricket_bat_art.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: linear-gradient(transparent, transparent), url(&quot;/w/resources/src/mediawiki.skinning/images/magnify-clip-ltr.svg?8330e&quot;); background-position-x: initial, initial; background-position-y: initial, initial; background-size: initial, initial; background-repeat: repeat, repeat; background-attachment: initial, initial; background-origin: initial, initial; background-clip: initial, initial; display: block; text-indent: 15px; white-space: nowrap; overflow: hidden; width: 15px; height: 11px; user-select: none;\"></a></div>Evolution of the cricket bat. The original \"<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hockey_stick\" title=\"Hockey stick\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">hockey stick</a>\" (left) evolved into the straight bat from c. 1760 when&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pitched_delivery_bowling\" title=\"Pitched delivery bowling\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">pitched delivery bowling</a>&nbsp;began.</div></div></div><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Although the main object of the game has always been to score the most&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Run_(cricket)\" title=\"Run (cricket)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">runs</a>, the early form of cricket differed from the modern game in certain key technical aspects; the North American variant of cricket known as&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wicket_(sport)\" title=\"Wicket (sport)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">wicket</a>&nbsp;retained many of these aspects.<sup id=\"cite_ref-14\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-14\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[14]</a></sup>&nbsp;The&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket_ball\" title=\"Cricket ball\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">ball</a>&nbsp;was&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Underarm_bowling\" title=\"Underarm bowling\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">bowled underarm</a>&nbsp;by the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bowling_(cricket)\" title=\"Bowling (cricket)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">bowler</a>&nbsp;and along the ground towards a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Batting_(cricket)\" title=\"Batting (cricket)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">batsman</a>&nbsp;armed with a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket_bat\" title=\"Cricket bat\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">bat</a>&nbsp;that, in shape, resembled a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hockey_stick\" title=\"Hockey stick\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">hockey stick</a>; the batsman defended a low, two-stump&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wicket\" title=\"Wicket\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">wicket</a>; and runs were called notches because the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scoring_(cricket)\" title=\"Scoring (cricket)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">scorers</a>&nbsp;recorded them by notching tally sticks.<sup id=\"cite_ref-DB9_15-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-DB9-15\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[15]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-BWC2_16-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-BWC2-16\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[16]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-JM21_17-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-JM21-17\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[17]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">In 1611, the year Cotgrave\'s dictionary was published,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ecclesiastical_court\" title=\"Ecclesiastical court\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">ecclesiastical court</a>&nbsp;records at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sidlesham\" title=\"Sidlesham\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Sidlesham</a>&nbsp;in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sussex\" title=\"Sussex\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Sussex</a>&nbsp;state that two parishioners, Bartholomew Wyatt and Richard Latter, failed to attend church on Easter Sunday because they were playing cricket. They were fined 12<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Penny_(British_pre-decimal_coin)\" title=\"Penny (British pre-decimal coin)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">d</a>&nbsp;each and ordered to do&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Penance\" title=\"Penance\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">penance</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-18\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-18\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[18]</a></sup>&nbsp;This is the earliest mention of adult participation in cricket and it was around the same time that the earliest known organised inter-parish or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Village_cricket\" title=\"Village cricket\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">village</a>&nbsp;match was played – at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chevening,_Kent\" title=\"Chevening, Kent\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Chevening, Kent</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-HSA21_6-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-HSA21-6\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[6]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-DU4_19-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-DU4-19\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[19]</a></sup>&nbsp;In 1624, a player called&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jasper_Vinall\" title=\"Jasper Vinall\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Jasper Vinall</a>&nbsp;died after he was accidentally struck on the head during a match between two parish teams in Sussex.<sup id=\"cite_ref-20\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-20\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[20]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Cricket remained a low-key local pursuit for much of the 17th century.<sup id=\"cite_ref-JM31_10-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-JM31-10\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[10]</a></sup>&nbsp;It is known, through numerous references found in the records of ecclesiastical court cases, to have been proscribed at times by the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Puritans\" title=\"Puritans\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Puritans</a>&nbsp;before and during the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Commonwealth_of_England\" title=\"Commonwealth of England\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Commonwealth</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-21\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-21\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[21]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-DU11_22-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-DU11-22\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[22]</a></sup>&nbsp;The problem was nearly always the issue of Sunday play as the Puritans considered cricket to be \"profane\" if played on the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sabbath\" title=\"Sabbath\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Sabbath</a>, especially if large crowds or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gambling\" title=\"Gambling\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">gambling</a>&nbsp;were involved.<sup id=\"cite_ref-DB7_23-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-DB7-23\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[23]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-JM23_24-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-JM23-24\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[24]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">According to the social historian&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Derek_Birley\" title=\"Derek Birley\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Derek Birley</a>, there was a \"great upsurge of sport after the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/English_Restoration\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"English Restoration\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Restoration</a>\" in 1660.<sup id=\"cite_ref-DB11_25-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-DB11-25\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[25]</a></sup>&nbsp;Gambling on sport became a problem significant enough for Parliament to pass the 1664 Gambling Act, limiting stakes to £100 which was, in any case, a colossal sum exceeding the annual income of 99% of the population.<sup id=\"cite_ref-DB11_25-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-DB11-25\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[25]</a></sup>&nbsp;Along with&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prizefighting\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Prizefighting\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">prizefighting</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Horse_racing\" title=\"Horse racing\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">horse racing</a>&nbsp;and blood sports, cricket was perceived to be a gambling sport.<sup id=\"cite_ref-26\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-26\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[26]</a></sup>&nbsp;Rich patrons made matches for high stakes, forming teams in which they engaged the first professional players.<sup id=\"cite_ref-RW10_27-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-RW10-27\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[27]</a></sup>&nbsp;By the end of the century, cricket had developed into a major sport that was spreading throughout England and was already being taken abroad by English mariners and colonisers – the earliest reference to cricket overseas is dated 1676.<sup id=\"cite_ref-28\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-28\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[28]</a></sup>&nbsp;A 1697 newspaper report survives of \"a great cricket match\" played in Sussex \"for fifty guineas apiece\" – this is the earliest known contest that is generally considered a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/First-class_cricket\" title=\"First-class cricket\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">First Class</a>&nbsp;match.<sup id=\"cite_ref-29\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-29\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[29]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-30\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-30\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[30]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">The patrons, and other players from the social class known as the \"<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gentry\" title=\"Gentry\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">gentry</a>\", began to classify themselves as \"<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amateur_status_in_first-class_cricket\" title=\"Amateur status in first-class cricket\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">amateurs</a>\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-amateur_31-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-amateur-31\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[fn 1]</a></sup>&nbsp;to establish a clear distinction from the professionals, who were invariably members of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Working_class\" title=\"Working class\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">working class</a>, even to the point of having separate changing and dining facilities.<sup id=\"cite_ref-32\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-32\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[31]</a></sup>&nbsp;The gentry, including such high-ranking nobles as the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Duke_of_Richmond\" title=\"Duke of Richmond\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Dukes of Richmond</a>, exerted their honour code of&nbsp;<i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Noblesse_oblige\" title=\"Noblesse oblige\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">noblesse oblige</a></i>&nbsp;to claim rights of leadership in any sporting contests they took part in, especially as it was necessary for them to play alongside their \"social inferiors\" if they were to win their bets.<sup id=\"cite_ref-DB19_33-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-DB19-33\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[32]</a></sup>&nbsp;In time, a perception took hold that the typical amateur who played in first-class cricket, until 1962 when amateurism was abolished, was someone with a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Public_school_(United_Kingdom)\" title=\"Public school (United Kingdom)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">public school</a>&nbsp;education who had then gone to one of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University_of_Cambridge\" title=\"University of Cambridge\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Cambridge</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University_of_Oxford\" title=\"\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Oxford University</a>&nbsp;– society insisted that such people were \"officers and gentlemen\" whose destiny was to provide leadership.<sup id=\"cite_ref-CW23_34-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-CW23-34\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[33]</a></sup>&nbsp;In a purely financial sense, the cricketing amateur would theoretically claim expenses for playing while his professional counterpart played under contract and was paid a wage or match fee; in practice, many amateurs claimed more than actual expenditure and the derisive term \"shamateur\" was coined to describe the practice.<sup id=\"cite_ref-35\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-35\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[34]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-DB146_36-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-DB146-36\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[35]</a></sup></p><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 0.3em 0px 0px; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-weight: bold; font-family: sans-serif;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"English_cricket_in_the_18th_and_19th_centuries\">English cricket in the 18th and 19th centuries</span></h3><div class=\"thumb tright\" style=\"clear: right; float: right; margin: 0.5em 0px 1.3em 1.4em; width: auto; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"min-width: 100px; border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); padding: 3px; background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); font-size: 13.16px; text-align: center; overflow: hidden; width: 172px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Francis_Cotes_-_The_young_cricketer_(1768).jpg\" class=\"image\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a9/Francis_Cotes_-_The_young_cricketer_%281768%29.jpg/170px-Francis_Cotes_-_The_young_cricketer_%281768%29.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"170\" height=\"261\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a9/Francis_Cotes_-_The_young_cricketer_%281768%29.jpg/255px-Francis_Cotes_-_The_young_cricketer_%281768%29.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a9/Francis_Cotes_-_The_young_cricketer_%281768%29.jpg/340px-Francis_Cotes_-_The_young_cricketer_%281768%29.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"3060\" data-file-height=\"4690\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"></a><div class=\"thumbcaption\" style=\"border: 0px; line-height: 1.4em; padding: 3px; font-size: 12.3704px; text-align: left;\"><div class=\"magnify\" style=\"float: right; margin-left: 3px; margin-right: 0px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Francis_Cotes_-_The_young_cricketer_(1768).jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: linear-gradient(transparent, transparent), url(&quot;/w/resources/src/mediawiki.skinning/images/magnify-clip-ltr.svg?8330e&quot;); background-position-x: initial, initial; background-position-y: initial, initial; background-size: initial, initial; background-repeat: repeat, repeat; background-attachment: initial, initial; background-origin: initial, initial; background-clip: initial, initial; display: block; text-indent: 15px; white-space: nowrap; overflow: hidden; width: 15px; height: 11px; user-select: none;\"></a></div><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Francis_Cotes\" title=\"Francis Cotes\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Francis Cotes</a>,&nbsp;<i>The Young Cricketer</i>, 1768</div></div></div><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">The game underwent major development in the 18th century to become England\'s national sport.<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\" style=\"line-height: 1; font-size: 11.2px; white-space: nowrap;\">[<i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (September 2017)\">citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup>&nbsp;Its success was underwritten by the twin necessities of patronage and betting.<sup id=\"cite_ref-37\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-37\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[36]</a></sup>&nbsp;Cricket was prominent in London as early as 1707 and, in the middle years of the century, large crowds flocked to matches on the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Artillery_Ground\" title=\"Artillery Ground\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Artillery Ground</a>&nbsp;in Finsbury.<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\" style=\"line-height: 1; font-size: 11.2px; white-space: nowrap;\">[<i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (September 2017)\">citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup>&nbsp;The&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Single_wicket_cricket\" title=\"Single wicket cricket\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">single wicket</a>&nbsp;form of the sport attracted huge crowds and wagers to match, its popularity peaking in the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1748_English_cricket_season\" title=\"1748 English cricket season\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">1748 season</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-ASW_38-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-ASW-38\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[37]</a></sup>&nbsp;Bowling underwent an evolution around 1760 when bowlers began to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pitched_delivery_bowling\" title=\"Pitched delivery bowling\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">pitch the ball</a>&nbsp;instead of rolling or skimming it towards the batsman. This caused a revolution in bat design because, to deal with the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bouncing_ball\" title=\"Bouncing ball\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">bouncing ball</a>, it was necessary to introduce the modern straight bat in place of the old \"hockey stick\" shape.<sup id=\"cite_ref-39\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-39\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[38]</a></sup><sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\" style=\"line-height: 1; font-size: 11.2px; white-space: nowrap;\">[<i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (September 2017)\">citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">The&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hambledon_Club\" title=\"Hambledon Club\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Hambledon Club</a>&nbsp;was founded in the 1760s and, for the next twenty years until the formation of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marylebone_Cricket_Club\" title=\"Marylebone Cricket Club\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Marylebone Cricket Club</a>&nbsp;(MCC) and the opening of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lord%27s_Old_Ground\" title=\"Lord\'s Old Ground\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Lord\'s Old Ground</a>&nbsp;in 1787, Hambledon was both the game\'s greatest club and its focal point.<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\" style=\"line-height: 1; font-size: 11.2px; white-space: nowrap;\">[<i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (September 2017)\">citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup>&nbsp;MCC quickly became the sport\'s premier club and the custodian of the&nbsp;<i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Laws_of_Cricket\" title=\"Laws of Cricket\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Laws of Cricket</a></i>. New Laws introduced in the latter part of the 18th century included the three stump wicket and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leg_before_wicket\" title=\"Leg before wicket\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">leg before wicket</a>&nbsp;(lbw).<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCA63_40-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-WCA63-40\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[39]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">The 19th century saw&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Underarm_bowling\" title=\"Underarm bowling\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">underarm bowling</a>&nbsp;superseded by first&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roundarm_bowling\" title=\"Roundarm bowling\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">roundarm</a>&nbsp;and then&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Overarm_bowling\" title=\"Overarm bowling\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">overarm bowling</a>. Both developments were controversial.<sup id=\"cite_ref-41\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-41\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[40]</a></sup>&nbsp;Organisation of the game at county level led to the creation of the county clubs, starting with&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sussex_County_Cricket_Club\" title=\"Sussex County Cricket Club\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Sussex</a>&nbsp;in 1839.<sup id=\"cite_ref-42\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-42\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[41]</a></sup>&nbsp;In December 1889, the eight leading county clubs formed the official&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/County_Championship\" title=\"County Championship\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">County Championship</a>, which began in 1890.<sup id=\"cite_ref-AMCS_43-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-AMCS-43\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[42]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">The most famous player of the 19th century was&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/W._G._Grace\" title=\"W. G. Grace\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">W. G. Grace</a>, who started his long and influential career in 1865. It was especially during the career of Grace that the distinction between amateurs and professionals became blurred by the existence of players like him who were nominally amateur but, in terms of their financial gain,&nbsp;<i>de facto</i>&nbsp;professional. Grace himself was said to have been paid more money for playing cricket than any professional.<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\" style=\"line-height: 1; font-size: 11.2px; white-space: nowrap;\">[<i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (September 2017)\">citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">The last two decades before the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_War_I\" title=\"World War I\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">First World War</a>&nbsp;have been called the \"<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Golden_Age_of_cricket\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Golden Age of cricket\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Golden Age of cricket</a>\". It is a nostalgic name prompted by the collective sense of loss resulting from the war, but the period did produce some great players and memorable matches, especially as organised competition at county and Test level developed.<sup id=\"cite_ref-44\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-44\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[43]</a></sup></p><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 0.3em 0px 0px; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-weight: bold; font-family: sans-serif;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Cricket_becomes_an_international_sport\">Cricket becomes an international sport</span></h3><div class=\"thumb tright\" style=\"clear: right; float: right; margin: 0.5em 0px 1.3em 1.4em; width: auto; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"min-width: 100px; border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); padding: 3px; background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); font-size: 13.16px; text-align: center; overflow: hidden; width: 222px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:England_in_North_America_1859.jpg\" class=\"image\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/84/England_in_North_America_1859.jpg/220px-England_in_North_America_1859.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"220\" height=\"151\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/84/England_in_North_America_1859.jpg/330px-England_in_North_America_1859.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/84/England_in_North_America_1859.jpg/440px-England_in_North_America_1859.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"937\" data-file-height=\"643\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"></a><div class=\"thumbcaption\" style=\"border: 0px; line-height: 1.4em; padding: 3px; font-size: 12.3704px; text-align: left;\"><div class=\"magnify\" style=\"float: right; margin-left: 3px; margin-right: 0px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:England_in_North_America_1859.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: linear-gradient(transparent, transparent), url(&quot;/w/resources/src/mediawiki.skinning/images/magnify-clip-ltr.svg?8330e&quot;); background-position-x: initial, initial; background-position-y: initial, initial; background-size: initial, initial; background-repeat: repeat, repeat; background-attachment: initial, initial; background-origin: initial, initial; background-clip: initial, initial; display: block; text-indent: 15px; white-space: nowrap; overflow: hidden; width: 15px; height: 11px; user-select: none;\"></a></div>The first English team to tour overseas, on board ship to North America, 1859</div></div></div><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Meanwhile, the British Empire had been instrumental in spreading the game overseas and by the middle of the 19th century it had become well established in Australia, the Caribbean, India, New Zealand, North America and South Africa.<sup id=\"cite_ref-45\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-45\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[44]</a></sup>&nbsp;In 1844, the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_v_Canada_(1844)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"United States v Canada (1844)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">first-ever international match</a>&nbsp;took place between the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_national_cricket_team\" title=\"United States national cricket team\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">United States</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canada_national_cricket_team\" title=\"Canada national cricket team\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Canada</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-46\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-46\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[45]</a></sup>&nbsp;In 1859, a team of English players went to North America on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/English_cricket_team_in_North_America_in_1859\" title=\"English cricket team in North America in 1859\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">the first overseas tour</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-47\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-47\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[46]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">In 1862, an English team made the first tour of Australia.<sup id=\"cite_ref-48\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-48\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[47]</a></sup>&nbsp;The first Australian team to travel overseas consisted of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indigenous_Australians\" title=\"Indigenous Australians\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Aboriginal</a>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stockman_(Australia)\" title=\"Stockman (Australia)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">stockmen</a>&nbsp;who&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australian_Aboriginal_cricket_team_in_England_in_1868\" title=\"Australian Aboriginal cricket team in England in 1868\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">toured England in 1868</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-49\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-49\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[48]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">In 1876–77, an&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/England_cricket_team\" title=\"England cricket team\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">England team</a>&nbsp;took part in what was retrospectively recognised as the first-ever&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Test_cricket\" title=\"Test cricket\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Test match</a>&nbsp;at the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Melbourne_Cricket_Ground\" title=\"Melbourne Cricket Ground\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Melbourne Cricket Ground</a>&nbsp;against&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australia_national_cricket_team\" title=\"Australia national cricket team\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Australia</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-50\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-50\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[49]</a></sup>&nbsp;The rivalry between England and Australia gave birth to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Ashes\" title=\"The Ashes\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The Ashes</a>&nbsp;in 1882, and this has remained Test cricket\'s most famous contest.<sup id=\"cite_ref-51\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-51\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[50]</a></sup>&nbsp;Test cricket began to expand in 1888–89 when&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Africa_national_cricket_team\" title=\"South Africa national cricket team\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">South Africa</a>&nbsp;played England.<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\" style=\"line-height: 1; font-size: 11.2px; white-space: nowrap;\">[<i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (September 2017)\">citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup></p><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 0.3em 0px 0px; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-weight: bold; font-family: sans-serif;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"World_cricket_in_the_20th_century\">World cricket in the 20th century</span></h3><div class=\"thumb tright\" style=\"clear: right; float: right; margin: 0.5em 0px 1.3em 1.4em; width: auto; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"min-width: 100px; border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); padding: 3px; background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); font-size: 13.16px; text-align: center; overflow: hidden; width: 172px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Bradman%26Bat.jpg\" class=\"image\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/19/Bradman%26Bat.jpg/170px-Bradman%26Bat.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"170\" height=\"222\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/19/Bradman%26Bat.jpg/255px-Bradman%26Bat.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/19/Bradman%26Bat.jpg/340px-Bradman%26Bat.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"615\" data-file-height=\"802\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"></a><div class=\"thumbcaption\" style=\"border: 0px; line-height: 1.4em; padding: 3px; font-size: 12.3704px; text-align: left;\"><div class=\"magnify\" style=\"float: right; margin-left: 3px; margin-right: 0px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Bradman%26Bat.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: linear-gradient(transparent, transparent), url(&quot;/w/resources/src/mediawiki.skinning/images/magnify-clip-ltr.svg?8330e&quot;); background-position-x: initial, initial; background-position-y: initial, initial; background-size: initial, initial; background-repeat: repeat, repeat; background-attachment: initial, initial; background-origin: initial, initial; background-clip: initial, initial; display: block; text-indent: 15px; white-space: nowrap; overflow: hidden; width: 15px; height: 11px; user-select: none;\"></a></div><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Don_Bradman\" title=\"Don Bradman\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Don Bradman</a>&nbsp;of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australia_national_cricket_team\" title=\"Australia national cricket team\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Australia</a>&nbsp;had a record Test batting average of 99.94.</div></div></div><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">The inter-war years were dominated by&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australia_national_cricket_team\" title=\"Australia national cricket team\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Australia</a>\'s&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Don_Bradman\" title=\"University of Oxford\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Don Bradman</a>, statistically the greatest Test batsman of all time. Test cricket continued to expand during the 20th century with the addition of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/West_Indies_cricket_team\" title=\"West Indies cricket team\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">West Indies</a>&nbsp;(1928),&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_Zealand_national_cricket_team\" title=\"\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">New Zealand</a>&nbsp;(1930) and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India_national_cricket_team\" title=\"India national cricket team\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">India</a>&nbsp;(1932) before the Second World War and then&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pakistan_national_cricket_team\" title=\"Pakistan national cricket team\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Pakistan</a>&nbsp;(1952),&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sri_Lanka_national_cricket_team\" title=\"Sri Lanka national cricket team\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Sri Lanka</a>&nbsp;(1982),&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zimbabwe_national_cricket_team\" title=\"Zimbabwe national cricket team\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Zimbabwe</a>&nbsp;(1992),&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bangladesh_national_cricket_team\" title=\"Bangladesh national cricket team\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Bangladesh</a>&nbsp;(2000),&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ireland_national_cricket_team\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ireland national cricket team\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Ireland</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afghanistan_national_cricket_team\" title=\"Afghanistan national cricket team\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Afghanistan</a>&nbsp;(both 2018) in the post-war period.<sup id=\"cite_ref-52\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-52\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[51]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-53\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-53\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[52]</a></sup>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Africa_cricket_team\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"South Africa cricket team\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">South Africa</a>&nbsp;was banned from international cricket from 1970 to 1992 as part of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sporting_boycott_of_South_Africa_during_the_apartheid_era\" title=\"Sporting boycott of South Africa during the apartheid era\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">apartheid boycott</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-54\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-54\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[53]</a></sup></p>', '<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><b>Cricket</b>&nbsp;is a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bat-and-ball_games\" title=\"Bat-and-ball games\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">bat-and-ball game</a>&nbsp;played between two teams of eleven players on a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket_field\" title=\"Cricket field\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">field</a>&nbsp;at the centre of which is a 22-yard (20-metre)&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket_pitch\" title=\"Cricket pitch\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">pitch</a>&nbsp;with a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wicket\" title=\"Wicket\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">wicket</a>&nbsp;at each end, each comprising two&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bail_(cricket)\" title=\"Bail (cricket)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">bails</a>&nbsp;balanced on three&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stump_(cricket)\" title=\"Stump (cricket)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">stumps</a>. The&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Batting_(cricket)\" title=\"Batting (cricket)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">batting</a>&nbsp;side scores&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Run_(cricket)\" title=\"Run (cricket)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">runs</a>&nbsp;by striking the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket_ball\" title=\"Cricket ball\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">ball</a>&nbsp;bowled at the wicket with the bat (and running between the wickets), while the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bowling_(cricket)\" title=\"Bowling (cricket)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">bowling</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fielding_(cricket)\" title=\"Fielding (cricket)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">fielding</a>&nbsp;side tries to prevent this (by preventing the ball from leaving the field, and getting the ball to either wicket) and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dismissal_(cricket)\" title=\"Dismissal (cricket)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">dismiss</a>&nbsp;each batter (so they are \"out\"). Means of dismissal include being&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bowled\" title=\"Bowled\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">bowled</a>, when the ball hits the stumps and dislodges the bails, and by the fielding side either&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caught\" title=\"Caught\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">catching</a>&nbsp;the ball after it is hit by the bat and before it hits the ground, or hitting a wicket with the ball before a batter can cross the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crease_(cricket)\" title=\"Crease (cricket)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">crease</a>&nbsp;in front of the wicket. When ten batters have been dismissed, the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Innings\" title=\"Innings\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">innings</a>&nbsp;ends and the teams swap roles. The game is adjudicated by two&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Umpire_(cricket)\" title=\"Umpire (cricket)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">umpires</a>, aided by a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Third_umpire\" title=\"Third umpire\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">third umpire</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Match_referee\" title=\"Match referee\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">match referee</a>&nbsp;in international matches.</p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Forms_of_cricket\" title=\"Forms of cricket\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Forms of cricket</a>&nbsp;range from&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Twenty20\" title=\"Twenty20\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Twenty20</a>, with each team batting for a single innings of 20&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Over_(cricket)\" title=\"Over (cricket)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">overs</a>, to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Test_cricket\" title=\"Test cricket\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Test matches</a>&nbsp;played over five days. Traditionally cricketers play in all-white&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket_clothing_and_equipment\" title=\"Cricket clothing and equipment\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">kit</a>, but in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Limited_overs_cricket\" title=\"Limited overs cricket\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">limited overs cricket</a>&nbsp;they wear club or team colours. In addition to the basic kit, some players wear&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket_clothing_and_equipment\" title=\"Cricket clothing and equipment\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">protective gear</a>&nbsp;to prevent injury caused by the ball, which is a hard, solid spheroid made of compressed&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leather\" title=\"Leather\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">leather</a>&nbsp;with a slightly raised sewn seam enclosing a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cork_(material)\" title=\"Cork (material)\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">cork</a>&nbsp;core layered with tightly wound string.</p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><img src=\"/media/common_media/MF8I7W1624701907.jpg\" data-filename=\"common_media/MF8I7W1624701907.jpg\"><br></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">The earliest reference to cricket is in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_East_England\" title=\"South East England\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">South East England</a>&nbsp;in the mid-16th century. It spread globally with the expansion of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British_Empire\" title=\"British Empire\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">British Empire</a>, with the first international matches in the second half of the 19th century. The game\'s governing body is the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Cricket_Council\" title=\"International Cricket Council\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">International Cricket Council</a>&nbsp;(ICC), which has over 100 members, twelve of which are&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_International_Cricket_Council_members\" title=\"List of International Cricket Council members\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">full members</a>&nbsp;who play Test matches. The game\'s rules, the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Laws_of_Cricket\" title=\"Laws of Cricket\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Laws of Cricket</a>, are maintained by&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marylebone_Cricket_Club\" title=\"Marylebone Cricket Club\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Marylebone Cricket Club</a>&nbsp;(MCC) in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/London\" title=\"London\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">London</a>. The sport is followed primarily in the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indian_subcontinent\" title=\"Indian subcontinent\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Indian subcontinent</a>, Australasia, the United Kingdom,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Southern_Africa\" title=\"Southern Africa\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">southern Africa</a>&nbsp;and the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/West_Indies\" title=\"West Indies\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">West Indies</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#cite_note-1\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[1]</a></sup>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Women%27s_cricket\" title=\"Women\'s cricket\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Women\'s cricket</a>, which is organised and played separately, has also achieved international standard. The most successful side playing&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_cricket\" title=\"International cricket\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">international cricket</a>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australia_national_cricket_team\" title=\"Australia national cricket team\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Australia</a>, which has won seven&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One_Day_International\" title=\"One Day International\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">One Day International</a>&nbsp;trophies, including five&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket_World_Cup\" title=\"Cricket World Cup\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">World Cups</a>, more than any other country and has been the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ICC_Test_Championship\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"ICC Test Championship\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">top-rated Test side</a>&nbsp;more than any other country.</p><div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\" role=\"navigation\" aria-labelledby=\"mw-toc-heading\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); padding: 7px; font-size: 13.3px; display: table; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif;\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"position: absolute; opacity: 0; z-index: -1; display: none; direction: ltr;\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"direction: ltr; text-align: center;\"><h2 id=\"mw-toc-heading\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 1em 0px 0.25em; padding: 0px; overflow: hidden; border: 0px; font-size: 13.3px; font-weight: bold; font-family: sans-serif; line-height: 1.3; display: inline;\">Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\" style=\"font-size: 12.502px;\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"cursor: pointer; color: rgb(6, 69, 173);\"></label></span></div><ul style=\"list-style: none; margin: 0.3em 0px; padding: 0px;\"><li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.1em;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket#History\" style=\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span class=\"tocnumber\" style=\"display: table-cell; text-decoration: inherit; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0.5em;\">1</span><span class=\"toctext\" style=\"display: table-cell; text-decoration: inherit;\">History</span></a><u