(2, 'BTOB Ex-Member Jung Il-hoon Sentenced 2 Years In Prison For The Use Of Marijuana | Net Worth & Girlfriend', 'btob-ex-member-jung-il-hoon-sentenced-2-years-in-prison-for-the-use-of-marijuana-net-worth-girlfriend', 'BTOB Ex-Member Jung Il-hoon Sentenced 2 Years In Prison For The Use Of Marijuana | Net Worth & Girlfriend', '\\images\\blogimages\\4305Y71625106721.jpg', '<p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;; font-size: 13.3333px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Jung Il-hoon, known as Ilhoon, is a South Korean rapper, songwriter, record producer, and actor. He was the main rapper of the South Korean boy band BtoB. He is well known for his collaborations with artists such as Hyuna and G.NA and for being an assistant MC on the variety show Weekly Idol.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;; font-size: 13.3333px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">He was born on 4 October 1994 in Samseong-dong, Seoul, South Korea. He is currently 26 years old. He is the younger brother of singer Joo. While he may be a talented personality, recently, he has been facing a legal problem.</span></p><h2 style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; font-family: &quot;droid sans&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); text-rendering: optimizelegibility; overflow-wrap: break-word; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Jung Il-hoon Sentenced 2 Years In Prison For The Use Of Marijuana</span></span></h2><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;; font-size: 13.3333px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">The singer Jung Il-hoon was&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.thestar.com.my/lifestyle/entertainment/2021/06/10/jung-ilhoon-of-k-pop-group-btob-sentenced-to-2-years-in-prison-fined-rm491k-for-buying-and-using-marijuana\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">sentenced to two years</a>&nbsp;in prison and fined 133 million won ($119,639) on 10 June 2021 for purchasing and using marijuana on 161 occasions, through three years starting from July 2016 up till January 2019.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;; font-size: 13.3333px; text-align: justify;\"><span id=\"ezoic-pub-video-placeholder-1\" class=\"ezoic-videopicker-video\"></span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Ilhoon was immediately taken into custody after the ruling was announced. He also had a group of seven accomplices with him, who were all sentenced to prison terms ranging from 1.5 to 2 years.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;; font-size: 13.3333px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Earlier, in the court hearing prior to this, the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://meaww.com/btob-eunkwang-public-apology-fans-questionable-controversial-gesture-ilhoon-departure-band-reactions\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">prosecutions demanded</a>&nbsp;a four-year prison sentence for Jung, along with the 133 million forfeiture. However, after this, Jung admitted to the charges and made a mercy plea, which led to a shorter sentence. The rapper had also left the boy band BtoB back in December 2020, after the news of his drug use came out.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;; font-size: 13.3333px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Last December, Korean channel Channel A reported that the police investigated Ilhoon for marijuana use, and the drug was detected in his hair. It said that to avoid detection, Ilhoon<a href=\"https://www.straitstimes.com/life/entertainment/former-btob-member-ilhoon-admits-to-buying-and-using-marijuana-at-first-court\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">&nbsp;used cryptocurrency to buy</a>&nbsp;marijuana. He deposited cash in an account of an acquaintance who converted it to cryptocurrency to buy marijuana.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;; font-size: 13.3333px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Ilhoon had&nbsp;<a href=\"https://voi.id/en/lifestyle/24828/tertangkap-konsumsi-mariyuana-ilhoon-pilih-keluar-dari-btob\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">postponed his mandatory military service</a>, which was supposed to be carried out in March due to the COVID-19 pandemic. However, the rapper recently served in the military during the year 2020.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;; font-size: 13.3333px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">When Ilhoon’s drug use allegations came to light, he was called up for trial in court on 22 April. According to the prosecution, Jung Ilhoon conspired with the other defendants from 6 July 2016 to 9 January 2019, spending over 130 million won ($116,400) for drugs and smoking a total of 826g marijuana 161 times.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;; font-size: 13.3333px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Ilhoon&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.kpopstarz.com/articles/298602/20210422/former-btob-ilhoon-admits-smoking-marijuana-161-times-first-trial.htm\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">admitted to his charges</a>,<span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">&nbsp;“I’m sincerely reflecting on my mistakes. I’m really sorry,”</span>&nbsp;the rapper said. The legal counsel noted,&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">“The defendant is reflecting deeply on his actions. He was fearful as it was the first trial and investigation of his life. He worked in the entertainment industry at such a young age and he tried to relieve the stress in the wrong way.”</span></span></p><h2 style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; font-family: &quot;droid sans&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); text-rendering: optimizelegibility; overflow-wrap: break-word; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Net Worth And Career Of Jung Il-hoon</span></span></h2><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;; font-size: 13.3333px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">With his endeavor throughout the years in the music industry, Jung Il-hoon has earned lots of fame and wealth in his name. Though his net worth is still in review, he may have accumulated millions of dollars to his name through his works in his professional career.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;; font-size: 13.3333px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">During G.NA’s debut promotion in 2010, Jung filled in some of Yong Junhyung’s parts during G.NA’s performance on a music show for the song<em>&nbsp;I’ll Back Off So You Can Live Better</em>. His debut as an actor was in 2011 through the JTBC sitcom&nbsp;<em>I Live</em>&nbsp;in Cheongdam Dong.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;; font-size: 13.3333px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Jung debuted as the main rapper of the boy band BtoB in 2012 with the group’s official debut on Mnet’s&nbsp;<em>M! Countdown</em>&nbsp;on 21 March 2021. The band BtoB became quite prominent in the Korean music industry,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.allkpop.com/article/2021/04/the-highest-earning-groups-based-on-their-appearance-fees-in-south-korea\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">earning them over</a>&nbsp;$45,000 per appearance in an event. Ilhoon also became a special MC along with Bomi from&nbsp;<em>Apink</em>&nbsp;from 2012 until the 206th&nbsp;episode. In 2015, he starred in the web drama, Webtoon Hero: Tundra Show as the lead actor, portraying Kim Sung-min.</span></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;; font-size: 13.3333px;\"><img class=\" jch-lazyloaded\" src=\"https://glamourbiz.com/images/uploads/jung-il-hoon-with-other-btob-members.jpg\" data-src=\"/images/uploads/jung-il-hoon-with-other-btob-members.jpg\" alt=\"jung il hoon with other btob members\" style=\"